<ref>{{cite web|last=Limbaugh |first=Rush |url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB123318906638926749.html |title=Rush Limbaugh: My Bipartisan Stimulus -- WSJ.com |publisher=Online.wsj.com |date=2009-01-29 |accessdate=2009-04-19}}</ref>。''Porkulus''（即译文中的“援猪”）为''pork''（猪）和''stimulus''（刺激）的复合词<ref>{{cite news |author=Tom Kuntz |url=http://ideas.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/02/08/porkulus/ |title=Idea of the Day: ‘Porkulus’ |date=2009-02-08 |accessdate=2009-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Ronald D. Utt, Ph.D. |url=http://www.heritage.org/research/budget/bg1266.cfm |title=How Congressional Earmarks and Pork-Barrel Spending Undermine State and Local Decisionmaking |date=1999-04-02 |accessdate=1999-04-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20021023150918/http://www.heritage.org/Research/Budget/BG1266.cfm |archivedate=2002-10-23 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Ronald D. Utt, Ph.D. |url=http://www.heritage.org/research/budget/wm608.cfm |title=Is Pork Barrel Spending Ready to Explode? The Anatomy of an Earmark |publisher=The Heritage Foundation |date=2004-11-10 |accessdate=2004-11-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041113041412/http://www.heritage.org/Research/Budget/wm608.cfm |archivedate=2004-11-13 }}</ref>。这个词迅速在保守派的政治家和时事评论员中流行开来，也表明了他们联合起来反对“增加政府开支拉动经济”政策的立场。

