根据[[合众社|合众社]]政治通讯员Liz Sidoti的说法，茶党运动“……是一场完全由人们自发的、经由互联网组织的运动。这是自由派和保守派的意识形态在缩减政府开支这一共识下的调和”<ref name=ap20100205>[http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_TEA_PARTY_POLITICS?SITE=AP&SECTION=HOME&TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&CTIME=2010-02-05-19-56-23 Where is "tea party" heading? Leaves are unclear]{{dead link|date=2018年4月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, Liz Sidoti, [[Associated_Press|AP]], 2010-02-05, accessed 2010-02-06.</ref>。他同时指出，“政府规模过大，开支不受控制，个人的自由正在受到威胁。奥巴马总统的政策正让这一切变得更糟糕。但是这也是为什么来自不同阶层的不满美国人能够团结在这一联盟（茶党运动）旗帜下的原因。”<ref name=ap20100205/>

茶党运动也有一些社会实体的参与，根据目标与方针的不同，可以分为：

* '''茶党爱国者（Tea Party Patriots）'''，这是一个在Freedomorks（由共和党前众议院多数党领袖Dick Armey领导的保守派非营利性组织）帮助下运作，自称有1000多个支部的全国性组织<ref>[http://www.wtok.com/news/headlines/53172462.html Grassroots Group Grabs Attention<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wtok.com/news/headlines/53172462.html |date=20110718123330 }}</ref><ref>[http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/health/2009607024_townhall06.html Health | Rowdy protests at health forums | Seattle Times Newspaper<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/alex-brantzawadzki/tea-party-convention-lose_b_416987.html Alex Brant-Zawadzki: Tea Party Convention Loses Main Sponsor<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.teapartypatriots.org/AboutUs.aspx Tea Party Patriots | About Tea Party Patriots<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100218062232/http://www.teapartypatriots.org/AboutUs.aspx |date=2010-02-18 }}</ref>。

* '''茶党快车'''，这是一个全国性的巴士旅游活动，由“国家需要更好的政治行动委员会”（一个位于[[萨克拉门托|萨克拉门托]]保守派的政治行动委员会）运作<ref name=autogenerated1 /><ref>[http://www.thenewamerican.com/index.php/usnews/politics/2766-turning-republicans-into-teapublicans Turning Republicans into Teapublicans<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.thesunchronicle.com/articles/2010/01/04/news/6669165.txt On board the Tea Party Express - The Sun Chronicle Online - News<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>。

* '''茶党国家'''于2010年2月4日至6日召集了一次“茶党全国大会”，前共和黨副總統候選人[[莎拉·佩林|莎拉·佩林]]是这次集会的演讲主宾，但此次大会高达$549的门票和佩琳价值$100,000的行头为人诟病<ref>[http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0130/Why-the-Tea-Party-Convention-is-tea-tering-on-the-edge Why the Tea Party Convention is tea-tering on the edge / The Christian Science Monitor - CSMonitor.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.startribune.com/blogs/81186517.html Palin, Bachmann Tea Party sessions closed to press | StarTribune.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/26/us/politics/26teaparty.html Tea Party Disputes Take Toll on Convention - NYTimes.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://firstread.msnbc.msn.com/archive/2010/01/15/2175393.aspx Tea Partying for profit? - First Read - msnbc.com<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100119183309/http://firstread.msnbc.msn.com/archive/2010/01/15/2175393.aspx |date=2010-01-19 }}</ref><ref>[http://lcn.canoe.ca/lcn/infos/lemonde/archives/2010/02/20100207-085944.html Palin prête pour une révolution]</ref>。佩琳称她会将所有收入捐给保守派运动<ref name="nytimes 02-06-10">{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/07/us/politics/08palin.html?hp|title=Palin Assails Obama at Tea Party Meeting|last=Zernike|first=Kate|date=February 6, 2010|publisher=New York Times}}</ref>。

根据[[CNN|CNN]]的投票调查显示，茶党运动大约80%的参与者是[[白人|白人]]（美国人口中白人比例大约为75%左右）<ref>[http://i2.cdn.turner.com/cnn/2010/images/02/17/rel4b.pdf CNN Poll]</ref><ref>U.S. Census Bureau; [http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-ds_name=ACS_2008_1YR_G00_&-CONTEXT=dt&-mt_name=ACS_2008_1YR_G2000_B02001&-redoLog=true&-geo_id=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en&-SubjectID=15233308] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20200212033754/http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-ds_name=ACS_2008_1YR_G00_&-CONTEXT=dt&-mt_name=ACS_2008_1YR_G2000_B02001&-redoLog=true&-geo_id=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en&-SubjectID=15233308 |date=2020-02-12 }}; Data Set: 2008 American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates; Survey: American Community Survey. Retrieved 2009-11-07</ref>。

== 社会反响 ==

=== 政界 ===
前众议院议长[[紐特·金里奇|紐特·金里奇]]政治活动小组美国方案（American Solutions）对茶党抗议表示了支持，他们在网站上写道“这是一个向华盛顿失败的政客和他们不负责任的政策表达反对和愤怒的机会”。金里奇在4月15日的[[纽约|纽约]]集会上也说过同样的话。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldmag.com/webextra/15293 |title="New York Tea Party," ''WORLD Magazine'', April 16, 2009 |publisher=Worldmag.com |date= |accessdate=2009-10-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090419060952/http://www.worldmag.com/webextra/15293 |archivedate=2009年4月19日 }}</ref>

[[德克萨斯州|德克萨斯州]]州长[[里克·佩里|里克·佩里]]参加了在[[奥斯汀|奥斯汀]]的一个茶党集会。他谈到了[[Youtube|Youtube]]上面的抗议影片<ref>[http://www.star-telegram.com/804/story/1313237.html Tax day 'tea parties' stir passion in Dallas-Fort Worth, U.S.]{{dead link|date=2018年4月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} ''[[Star_Telegram|Star Telegram]]''. Published April 12, 2009.</ref>。佩里还回答了一些关于德州独立的问题。他说：“（未来）有很多不同的可能。我们有一个很好的联邦，我们没有任何理由去破坏它。但是如果华盛顿继续忽视人民的呼声，谁知道将来会发生什么呢？德州是个非常特殊的省份，我们有很大的独立性。”<ref>{{cite web |author=By W. Gardner Selby, Jason Embry |url=http://www.statesman.com/news/content/region/legislature/stories/04/17/0417gop.html |title=Perry stands by secession comments |publisher=Statesman.com |date= |accessdate=2009-04-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090418214515/http://www.statesman.com/news/content/region/legislature/stories/04/17/0417gop.html |archivedate=2009-04-18 }}</ref>

茶党也得到了许多其他官员的赞扬。众议员Tom Price说抗议活动说明“这片土地还是人民做主的”。众议员Jeb Hensarling说茶党运动是“有益的”和“正大光明的”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rollcall.com/issues/54_151/news/36213-1.html |title="Anti-Tax Groups Reprise Tea Parties," ''Roll Call'', June 24, 2009 |publisher=Rollcall.com |date=2009-06-24 |accessdate=2009-10-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090628050028/http://www.rollcall.com/issues/54_151/news/36213-1.html |archivedate=2009年6月28日 }}</ref>。

脱口秀主持人Leslie Marshall将茶党运动与波士顿倾茶事件相比较，她说“如果你读过历史就会知道，人们当年抗税的原因就是他们没有代表权……但是奥巴马并不是要用苛捐杂税把你们逼到无路可退——他是打算拯救经济，而且他是民选的”<ref name=move>[http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/04/13/pub-moveon/ Move Over, MoveOn: Tea Parties Spark Conservative Insurgency Online] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091023204433/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/04/13/pub-moveon/ |date=2009-10-23 }}. By Judson Berger. [[Fox_News|Fox News]]. Published April 13, 2009.</ref>。政治评论员Bob Cesca评论说“现在邻居的瓦上霜也和你息息相关了，当社区中出现任何一间因为还贷不及时而被银行没收的房子的时候，你的房子价值也会跟着跳水”。历史学家，小布什时期的[[美国财政部|美国财政部]]官员Bruce Bartlett在《福布斯》上撰文称高税收未必如此糟糕，“高税收可以（令政府）提供更好的社会服务，因此它们并不像表面上看来那么难以承受”<ref name=time>[http://www.forbes.com/2009/04/09/tea-party-taxes-opinions-columnists-bartlett.html Tax Tea Party Time?] By Bruce Bartlett. ''[[Forbes|Forbes]]''. Published April 10, 2009.</ref>。

很多体制外的政治候选人也受到了茶党运动支持者的影响。共和黨参议员[[斯科特·布朗|斯科特·布朗]]就是因为茶党的支持在民主黨人佔優的[[马萨诸塞州|马萨诸塞州]]補选中意外获胜<ref>[http://www.csmonitor.com/Commentary/Opinion/2010/0119/Scott-Brown-the-tea-party-s-first-electoral-victory ''www.csmonitor.com'']</ref>。很多参与2010年选举的政治家都得到了来自茶党大众的支持，其中包括参加[[宾夕法尼亚|宾夕法尼亚]]州州长选举的共和党人Sam Rohrer，德州州长选举的Debra Medina和参议员候选人[[兰德·保罗|兰德·保罗]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://kdka.com/local/sam.rohrer.campaign.2.1441012.html |title=''www.kdka.com'' |access-date=2010-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100131075254/http://kdka.com/local/sam.rohrer.campaign.2.1441012.html |archive-date=2010-01-31 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>[http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2010/02/debra-medina-texas-gubernatori.html?wprss=44 ''www.washingtonpost.com'']</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.americasnewsonline.com/tea-party-movement-backing-kentucky-senate-race-leader-rand-paul-940/ |title=''americasnewsonline.com'' |access-date=2010-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100222121324/http://www.americasnewsonline.com/tea-party-movement-backing-kentucky-senate-race-leader-rand-paul-940/ |archive-date=2010-02-22 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

=== 工会 ===
一些工会领袖认为茶党运动是一些企业和集团资助的别有目的的活动，他们提倡人们以非暴力的形式反对茶党的抗议活动<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/08/06/unions-to-take-on-conserv_n_252720.html ''Unions To Take On Conservative Groups Health Care Town Halls''], Sam Stein, [[Huffington_Post|Huffington Post]], August 6, 2009</ref>，但事与愿违，在工会成员和茶党示威者对抗的过程中还是发生了暴力冲突。

=== 媒体 ===
根据《美国新闻与世界报道》（''US News and World Report''）的观点，茶党运动在全国各地的普遍出现本身就已经说明问题了<ref name=world/> 。

很多人都指出保守派媒體[[霍士新聞網|霍士新聞網]]（Fox News）对茶党运动有明显的偏袒，甚至还有人认为茶党运动最初就是由Fox News煽动的，另外有些人也抱怨在茶党运动的初期除了Fox News其它媒体对此运动毫不关心。

茶党运动被许多左翼自由派评论员嘲笑讥讽，其中包括[[MSNBC|MSNBC]]的Rachel Maddow<ref name =frat/>、Keith Olbermann、''The Young Turks''电台主持人<ref name =frat/> Cenk Uygur<ref name =frat/>、David Shuster<ref name =frat>[http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/04/16/cable-anchors-guests-use-tea-parties-platform-frat-house-humor/ Cable Anchors, Guests Use Tea Parties as Platform for Frat House Humor] {{Wayback|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2009/04/16/cable-anchors-guests-use-tea-parties-platform-frat-house-humor/ |date=20100915025853 }}, FOX News. Published April 16, 2009.</ref>、脱口秀主持人Leslie Marshall<ref name=move/>、经济学家Paul Krugman<ref name="paul">[http://www.nytimes.com/2009/04/13/opinion/13krugman.html?ref=opinion Tea Parties Forever]. By [[Paul_Krugman|Paul Krugman]]. ''[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]''. Published April 12, 2009.</ref>、Andrew Sullivan<ref>[http://andrewsullivan.theatlantic.com/the_daily_dish/2009/04/the-tea-tantrum-mystery.html#more The Tea Tantrum Mystery]. Published April 10, 2009.</ref>、公共政策律师团MoveOn.org<ref name=today/>、政治讽刺作家Jon Stewart<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/04/16/tempest-in-a-tea-party-th_n_187638.html]</ref>以及Thomas Frank<ref name="frank">[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/thomas-frank/conservatives-and-their-p_b_171877.html Conservatives and Their Pity Parties], [[Thomas_Frank|Thomas Frank]], March 4, 2009, ''[[The_Huffington_Post|The Huffington Post]]''</ref>。

但另一方面，茶党运动也得到了保守派评论员如Sean Hannity、Michelle Malkin、Glenn Beck<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.glennbeck.com/content/articles/article/198/23831/ |title="Glenn Beck: Tea Party" |date=2009-04-09 }}</ref> 以及Glenn Reynolds<ref name="sfexaminer">{{cite news|url=http://www.sfexaminer.com/opinion/Tea-parties-are-flash-crowds-Obama-should-fear-41547632.html|title=Tea parties are flash crowds Obama should fear|date=March 19, 2009|publisher=[[The_San_Francisco_Examiner|The San Francisco Examiner]]|first=Mark|last=Tapscott|accessdate=June 16, 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090419142317/http://www.sfexaminer.com/opinion/Tea-parties-are-flash-crowds-Obama-should-fear-41547632.html|archivedate=April 19, 2009}}</ref>，前众议院多数党领袖Dick Armey<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,516136,00.html |title=Dick Armey to Speak at Atlanta Tea Party |accessdate=2009-04-15|date=2009-04-15 }}</ref>，摇滚吉他手兼政治活动家Ted Nugent<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1609280/20090415/story.jhtml |title=What's A Tax Day Tea Party? |accessdate=2009-04-15|date=2009-04-15 }}</ref>、乡村音乐歌手John Rich<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gactv.com/gac/nw_headlines/article/0,3034,GAC_26063_5942336_01,00.html |title=John Rich Attends a Tea Party |accessdate=2009-04-14 |date=2009-04-15 }}{{dead link|date=2018年4月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>，前[[阿肯色州|阿肯色州]]州长共和党员[[麥克·赫卡比|麥克·赫卡比]](Mike Huckabee)和保守派广播电台Neal Boortz<ref name="MH">{{cite web |url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/233/story/666428.html |title=Supporters of national sales tax gather in SC |accessdate=2009-04-15 |date=2009-04-16 }}{{dead link|date=2018年4月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> 等人的支持。

一个名为“美国媒体事务”（Media Matters for America）的自命为为革新派的媒体监督组织认为，Fox News没能秉承中立报道的原则，他们对茶党运动的发展起到了推波助澜的作用，并且鼓励观众参与到茶党运动中去。这个组织列举了很多例子，比如Glenn Beck的剧集中一个外景就是茶党抗议的场面<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mediamatters.org/mmtv/200904060023 |title=Beck says you can "celebrate with Fox News" at any of four "FNC Tax Day Tea Parties" |publisher=mediamatters.com |date= |accessdate=2009-08-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090817171559/http://mediamatters.org/mmtv/200904060023 |archive-date=2009-08-17 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。“媒体事务” 的主席Eric Burns发表了一封致''Fox News Sunday''负责人Chris Wallace的公开信，要求后者承认Fox News“已经超越了媒体中立报道，以及依法不煽动政治活动的界线”<ref name=fox/>。他同时指出，Fox News“在10天内播送了至少107条支持茶党运动的商业广告”，进而导致了4月15日的抗议活动<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mediamatters.org/research/200904170011 |title=存档副本 |access-date=2010-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100124075220/http://mediamatters.org/research/200904170011 |archive-date=2010-01-24 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

在4月15日的一个抗议活动中，[[CNN|CNN]]记者Susan Roesgen采访了一些抗议者，并将该活动称为“反政府”、“反CNN”以及“由右翼保守派Fox News煽动的”。在周围的抗议者以脏话反击后，她说“我认为这里的情景已经不适合（有未成年的）家庭收看了，我现在将信号转回直播间”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mediabistro.com/tvnewser/cnn/partiedout_cnn_reporter_takes_a_break_114340.asp?c=rss |title=Partied-Out CNN Reporter |publisher=[[TV_Newser|TV Newser]] |accessdate=April 27, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090625224440/http://www.mediabistro.com/tvnewser/cnn/partiedout_cnn_reporter_takes_a_break_114340.asp?c=rss |archive-date=2009-06-25 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0904/15/cnr.06.html |title=CNN Transcript of Roesgen Tea Party report |publisher=Transcripts.cnn.com |date= |accessdate=2009-10-18}}</ref>。媒体研究中心（Media Research Center）新闻博客、《波士顿先锋报》专栏作家Michael Graham指茶黨運動不會結束，並對CNN報道提出批评。<ref>{{cite web |title=Tea Party won't end |publisher=Boston Herald |date=2009-04-17 |url=http://news.bostonherald.com/news/opinion/op_ed/view/2009_04_17_Tea_Party_won_t_end:_Our_cup_runneth_over/srvc=home&position=recent |accessdate=2009-04-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090420015813/http://news.bostonherald.com/news/opinion/op_ed/view/2009_04_17_Tea_Party_won_t_end%3A_Our_cup_runneth_over/srvc%3Dhome%26position%3Drecent |archivedate=2009-04-20 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title =Conspiricy [sic] News Network (CNN) Reporter: Tea Party’s Are Anti-Government, Anti-CNN |publisher=[[KXMB-TV|KXMB-TV]] |date=2009-04-15 |url=http://www.kxmb.com/News/Nation/361296.asp |accessdate=2009-04-15 |deadurl =yes | archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20090419132623/http://www.kxmb.com/News/Nation/361296.asp |archivedate=2009年4月19日 |df= }}</ref>她同时也得到了新闻博客[[Daily_Kos|Daily Kos]]编辑Jed Lewison的赞赏，Lewison同时反问“CNN什么时候才能反击”<ref>[http://www.dailykos.com/storyonly/2009/4/16/105346/004 When will CNN Fight Back?] Jed Lewison, Daily Kos TV 2009-04-16</ref>？[[乔治华盛顿大学|乔治华盛顿大学]]的媒体学教授Frank Sesno也为Roesgen背书，称赞她不和稀泥的报道<ref>{{cite web   | title =State of the Union with John King|publisher=CNN |date=2009-04-19 |url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0904/19/sotu.02.html|accessdate=2009-04-26 }}</ref>。CNN发言人称，“她只是履行她的职责，如实报道她所看到的情况”<ref>{{cite web |title=CNN Reporter at Chicago Tea Party |publisher=[[TV_Newser|TV Newser]] |date=2009-04-15 |url=http://www.mediabistro.com/tvnewser/cnn/cnn_reporter_at_chicago_tea_party_its_anticnn_since_this_is_highly_promoted_by_the_rightwing_conservative_network_fox_114141.asp |accessdate=2009-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090416230205/http://www.mediabistro.com/tvnewser/cnn/cnn_reporter_at_chicago_tea_party_its_anticnn_since_this_is_highly_promoted_by_the_rightwing_conservative_network_fox_114141.asp |archive-date=2009-04-16 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

